<p itemprop="description">Stakeholder relationship management involves identifying, engaging with, and managing relationships with individuals and groups who have an interest in or influence over organisational activities, projects, and outcomes.</p>

<div class="proficiency-levels">
    <h2>Proficiency Levels</h2>

    <ol class="skill-levels">
        <li>
            <h3>Awareness</h3>
            <p>You can identify key stakeholders and understand their different interests and levels of influence. You recognise the importance of stakeholder engagement in project success.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
            <h3>Working</h3>
            <p>You can engage with stakeholders effectively, manage basic stakeholder communications, and adapt your approach to different stakeholder needs and preferences.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
            <h3>Practitioner</h3>
            <p>You can develop comprehensive stakeholder strategies, facilitate complex stakeholder discussions, manage conflicting interests, and build strong working relationships across the organisation.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
            <h3>Expert</h3>
            <p>You can establish stakeholder management frameworks, influence strategic stakeholder relationships, resolve complex stakeholder conflicts, and mentor others in stakeholder engagement.</p>
        </li>
    </ol>
</div>

